message.content:
We need to calculate the following ratios using the information provided in the three financial statements. Let’s go through each step‐by‐step.

1. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio

• Formula: Operating Cash Flow ÷ Total Current Liabilities  
• Operating Cash Flow (from cash flow statement – “Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities”): –650630.22  
• Current Liabilities (from balance sheet – “Total Current Liabilities” at end): 628478.02  
• Calculation: –650630.22 ÷ 628478.02 ≈ –1.04

2. Debt to Equity Ratio

• Formula: Total Liabilities ÷ Total Owner’s Equity  
• In this balance sheet, the only liability presented is the current liabilities, which is 628478.02.  
• Total Owner’s Equity (from balance sheet – “Total Owner's Equity” at end): 13905750.76  
• Calculation: 628478.02 ÷ 13905750.76 ≈ 0.0452, which rounds to 0.05

3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio

• Formula: Total Revenue ÷ Total Assets  
• Total Revenue (from income statement): 2869560.42  
• Total Assets (from balance sheet – “Total Assets” at end): 14534228.78  
• Calculation: 2869560.42 ÷ 14534228.78 ≈ 0.1974, which rounds to 0.20

4. Quick Ratio

• Formula: (Current Assets – Inventory) ÷ Current Liabilities  
• Current Assets (from balance sheet – “Total Current Assets” at end): 9625738.03  
• Inventory (from balance sheet): 112000.00  
• Quick Assets = 9625738.03 – 112000.00 = 9513738.03  
• Current Liabilities: 628478.02  
• Calculation: 9513738.03 ÷ 628478.02 ≈ 15.15

5. Operating Cash Flow Ratio

• This ratio is calculated the same way as the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio.  
• Thus, it is –650630.22 ÷ 628478.02 ≈ –1.04

6. Return on Equity (ROE)

• Formula: Net Profit ÷ Total Owner’s Equity  
• Net Profit (from income statement): 905750.76  
• Total Owner’s Equity (from balance sheet): 13905750.76  
• Calculation: 905750.76 ÷ 13905750.76 ≈ 0.06515, which as a percentage is ≈ 6.52%

7. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio

• The typical formula is: Accounts Receivable Turnover = Total Revenue ÷ Average Accounts Receivable.  
• Accounts Receivable on the balance sheet increased from 0 (beginning) to 2149792.45 (end), so the average is: (0 + 2149792.45) ÷ 2 = 1074896.225  
• Total Revenue: 2869560.42  
• Calculation: 2869560.42 ÷ 1074896.225 ≈ 2.67

Now we put all the results into the required JSON output format.

{
  "solution": {
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-1.04",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.05",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.20",
    "Quick Ratio": "15.15",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.04",
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.52%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "2.67"
  }
}
